description.p:
Finally, the present invention relates to a method for inserting a weight with a device for inserting a balancing weight as defined above, characterized in that it successively comprises the following steps:
the turbine is stopped;
the rotor is orientated so that a balancing hole is opposite the second opening of the chamber of the device;
using the nut, the device is connected to the rotor so that the surface provided with the sealing joint of the internal component is in contact with the rotor;
the chamber of the device is opened by acting on the two screws, by removing the cap which closes the first opening of the chamber, which fills the chamber with air;
the weight is introduced into the hole of the rotor via the chamber of the device and it is positioned by means of screwing, then it is locked in position by means of caulking in the balancing hole which co-operates with a thread which is present on the weight;
the cap is repositioned in order to close the first opening of the chamber;
the device is disconnected from the rotor with the nut;
the turbine is put back into operation.

claim.claim-text:
A method for inserting a balancing weight into a rotor (43) of a turbine (4) using a device (1) as claimed in any one of claims 1 to 5, wherein the method includes the successively steps of:
- stopping the turbine (4);
- orientating the rotor (43) so that a balancing hole (44) is opposite the second opening (52) of the chamber (5) of the device (1);
- bringing the surface (53) of the sealing joint (54) of the internal component (11) in contact with the rotor (43) by use of the nut (2);
- opening the chamber (5) of the device by acting on the two screws (31) so as to remove the cap (3) which closes the first opening (51) of the chamber (5) thereby filing fill the chamber (5) with air;
- introducing the weight into the hole (44) of the rotor (43) via the chamber (5) of the device (1), positioning the weight by means of screwing and locking the weight into position by means of caulking in the balancing hole (44) that co-operates with a thread present on the weight;
- repositioning the cap (3) so as to close the first opening (51) of the chamber (5);
- using the nut to disconnected the device (1) from the rotor (43);
- returning the turbine (1) into operation.
